Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State on Friday said worship centres in the state will remain shut until further notice. Sanwo-Olu during a briefing at Alausa Ikeja, also stated that all restrictions applying to mass gatherings will remain in force. He also announced that social and events centres as well as social clubs will also remain closed. Recall that the governor had also said only students in transitional classes (Basic Six, JSS 3 and SS3) are permitted to resume from Monday, 3rd of August, 2020. He, however, added that the decision only applies only to day schooling.‚Äù